{"title_page": "Astral (1923 automobile)", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2017}}\n{{Use British English|date=July 2017}}\nThe '''Astral''' was a car built from 1923 to 1924 by Hertford Engineering Co Ltd, [[Barking, London|Barking]], then in [[Essex]] (now in east [[London]]), England. \n\nOnly one model was made, the 12/40, and although it was short-lived, it had many advanced features. The engine, made in-house, was a 1720&nbsp;cc four-cylinder with a single overhead camshaft, and the car had brakes on all four wheels. It cost \u00a3365 for a two-seater and \u00a3375 for a four/five-seat tourer. The number made is not known.\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of car manufacturers of the United Kingdom]]\n\n==References==\n*[[Georgano, G.N.]], \"Astral\", in G.N. Georgano, ed., ''The Complete Encyclopedia of Motorcars 1885-1968''  (New York: E.P. Dutton and Co., 1974), pp.56.\n\n[[Category:Defunct motor vehicle manufacturers of England]]\n[[Category:Companies based in the London Borough of Barking and Dagenham]]\n[[Category:Cars introduced in 1923]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2017}}\n{{Use British English|date=July 2017}}\nThe '''Astral''' was a car built from 1923 to 1924 by Hertford Engineering Co Ltd, [[Barking, London|Barking]], then in [[Essex]] (now in east [[London]]), England. \n\nOnly one model was made, the 12/40, and although it was short-lived, it had many advanced features. The engine, made in-house, was a 1720&nbsp;cc four-cylinder with a single overhead camshaft, and the car had brakes on all four wheels. It cost \u00a3365 for a two-seater and \u00a3375 for a four/five-seat tourer. The number made is not known.\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of car manufacturers of the United Kingdom]]\n\n==References==\n*[[Georgano, G.N.]], \"Astral\", in G.N. Georgano, ed., ''The Complete Encyclopedia of Motorcars 1885-1968''  (New York: E.P. Dutton and Co., 1974), pp.56.\n\n[[Category:Defunct motor vehicle manufacturers of England]]\n[[Category:Companies based in the London Borough of Barking and Dagenham]]\n", "name_user": "TKOIII", "label": "safe", "comment": "cat", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Astral_(1923_automobile)"}
{"title_page": "Naturschutzbund Deutschland", "text_new": "{{for|the computer system|NABU Network}}\n{{Coord|52.523136|N|13.378625|E|type:landmark_region:DE-BE|display=title|format=dms}}\n\n{{infobox organization/Wikidata \n| fetchwikidata = ALL \n| onlysourced = yes\n| image = NABU_logo_low_resolution.jpg|suppressfields=revenue membership staff\n}}\n\n[[File:Haus Wattwurm - Naturschutzzentrum im Speicherkoog Dithmarschen IMG 5963.JPG|thumb|NABU Station Haus Wattwurm on the Speicherkoog Dithmarschen]]\n\nThe '''Naturschutzbund Deutschland e.V.''' (\"'''Nature and Biodiversity Conservation Union'''\") or '''NABU''' is a German [[non-governmental organisation]] (NGO) dedicated to [[Conservation movement|conservation]] at home and abroad, including the protection of rivers, forests and individual species of animals.\n\n== General facts ==\nNABU is one of the largest, most well-known, nature conservation groups in Germany and has worked for over 100 years for man and nature. NABU carries out specific conservation projects, maintains a research institute, runs environmental training and informs the [[News media|media]] and public about important topics connected with the environment and nature conservation. The society is formally recognised by the German state as an environmental and conservation society, a body responsible for public issues (''Tr\u00e4ger \u00f6ffentlicher Belange''), and must therefore be consulted over issues affecting the [[ecology]].\n\nNABU has about 530,000 members ({{as of|lc=yes|June 2016}}) as active [[conservationists]] or supporters. They are organised into more than 1,800 local groups across Germany.\n\nNABU is the national partner organisation of [[BirdLife International]]. The organisation is one of the most significant members of the German umbrella organization of the German [[conservation movement]] [[Deutscher Naturschutzring]] (DNR).\n\n== History ==\nThe NABU was founded  by [[Lina H\u00e4hnle]] on 1 February 1899 in [[Stuttgart]] as the '''Bund f\u00fcr Vogelschutz''' ('''BfV''').\nIn 1990 the BfV merged with former [[DDR Naturschutz society]] to Naturschutzbund Deutschland (NABU). Since then, the focus got broader and NABU built up divisions for international conservation projects, [[Marine conservation|marine conservation]] and energy sufficiency.\n\n==Guides==\n[https://baden-wuerttemberg.nabu.de/umwelt-und-leben/natur-erleben/nabu-guides/oestlichealb.html NABU  Ostalb-Guides]\n[http://www.forbach.de/inhalte/tourismus/tourismusaktivwandernnabu.html NABU  Schwarzwald-Guides]\n[http://www4.um.baden-wuerttemberg.de/servlet/is/128469/ NABU  Neckar-Guides]\n[http://www4.um.baden-wuerttemberg.de/servlet/is/1858/ NABU  Mittlere Alb-Guides]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{commons cat|Naturschutzbund Deutschland}}\n* [http://www.nabu.de/ Official website of the NABU] {{in lang|de|en}}\n{{Authority control}}\n[[Category:Charities based in Germany]]\n[[Category:Environmental organisations based in Germany]]\n[[Category:Conservation organisations based in Germany]]\n[[Category:Organizations established in 1899]]\n[[Category:Non-profit organisations based in Berlin]]\n[[Category:1899 establishments in Germany]]\n[[Category:Organizations established in 1990]]\n[[Category:1990 establishments in Germany]]\n\n[[Category:Deutscher Naturschutzring]]\n{{Germany-org-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{for|the computer system|NABU Network}}\n{{Coord|52.523136|N|13.378625|E|type:landmark_region:DE-BE|display=title|format=dms}}\n\n{{infobox organization/Wikidata \n| fetchwikidata = ALL \n| onlysourced = yes\n| image = NABU_logo_low_resolution.jpg|suppressfields=revenue membership staff\n}}\n\n[[File:Haus Wattwurm - Naturschutzzentrum im Speicherkoog Dithmarschen IMG 5963.JPG|thumb|NABU Station Haus Wattwurm on the Speicherkoog Dithmarschen]]\n\nThe '''Naturschutzbund Deutschland e.V.''' (\"'''Nature and Biodiversity Conservation Union'''\") or '''NABU''' is a German [[non-governmental organisation]] (NGO) dedicated to [[Conservation movement|conservation]] at home and abroad, including the protection of rivers, forests and individual species of animals.\n\n== General facts ==\nNABU is one of the largest, most well-known, nature conservation groups in Germany and has worked for over 100 years for man and nature. NABU carries out specific conservation projects, maintains a research institute, runs environmental training and informs the [[News media|media]] and public about important topics connected with the environment and nature conservation. The society is formally recognised by the German state as an environmental and conservation society, a body responsible for public issues (''Tr\u00e4ger \u00f6ffentlicher Belange''), and must therefore be consulted over issues affecting the [[ecology]].\n\nNABU has about 530,000 members ({{as of|lc=yes|June 2016}}) as active [[conservationists]] or supporters. They are organised into more than 1,800 local groups across Germany.\n\nNABU is the national partner organisation of [[BirdLife International]]. The organisation is one of the most significant members of the German umbrella organization of the German [[conservation movement]] [[Deutscher Naturschutzring]] (DNR).\n\n== History ==\nThe NABU was founded  by [[Lina H\u00e4hnle]] on 1 February 1899 in [[Stuttgart]] as the '''Bund f\u00fcr Vogelschutz''' ('''BfV''').\nIn 1990 the BfV merged with former [[DDR Naturschutz society]] to Naturschutzbund Deutschland (NABU). Since then the focus got broader and NABU builded up devisions for international conservation projects, [[Marine conservation|marine conservation]] and energy sufficiency.\n\n==Guides==\n[https://baden-wuerttemberg.nabu.de/umwelt-und-leben/natur-erleben/nabu-guides/oestlichealb.html NABU  Ostalb-Guides]\n[http://www.forbach.de/inhalte/tourismus/tourismusaktivwandernnabu.html NABU  Schwarzwald-Guides]\n[http://www4.um.baden-wuerttemberg.de/servlet/is/128469/ NABU  Neckar-Guides]\n[http://www4.um.baden-wuerttemberg.de/servlet/is/1858/ NABU  Mittlere Alb-Guides]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{commons cat|Naturschutzbund Deutschland}}\n* [http://www.nabu.de/ Official website of the NABU] {{in lang|de|en}}\n{{Authority control}}\n[[Category:Charities based in Germany]]\n[[Category:Environmental organisations based in Germany]]\n[[Category:Conservation organisations based in Germany]]\n[[Category:Organizations established in 1899]]\n[[Category:Non-profit organisations based in Berlin]]\n[[Category:1899 establishments in Germany]]\n[[Category:Organizations established in 1990]]\n[[Category:1990 establishments in Germany]]\n\n[[Category:Deutscher Naturschutzring]]\n{{Germany-org-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Woodlot", "label": "safe", "comment": "spelling, punctuation", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Naturschutzbund_Deutschland"}
